<paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id3154248" xml-lang="en-US" level="1" l10n="U" oldref="11"><variable id="calculate_multitable"><link href="text/swriter/guide/calculate_multitable.xhp" name="Calculating Across Tables">Calculating Across Tables</link>
</variable></paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3147773" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="12">You can perform calculations that span across more than one table in a text document.</paragraph>
<list type="ordered">
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3147795" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="13">Open a text document, insert two tables, and type numbers in a few cells in both tables.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3147815" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="14">Place your cursor in an empty cell in one of the tables.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3147833" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="16">Press F2.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3147228" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="17">In the <emph>Formula Bar</emph>, enter the function that you want to perform, for example, "=SUM".</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3147254" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="18">Click in a cell containing a number, press the plus sign (+), and then click in a different cell containing a number.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3147274" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="19">Press <emph>Enter</emph>.</paragraph>
</listitem>
</list>
